An architect is reviewing an application's IAM Role and finds the following permission policy:
{ "Effect": "Allow", "Action": "*", "Resource": "*" }
A Permission Boundary is attached to the role with the following policy:
{ "Effect": "Allow", "Action": ["s3:GetObject", "s3:PutObject"], "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::app-bucket/*" }
The role attempts to call dynamodb:PutItem on a DynamoDB table. What is the result?
